{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5415,"text":"Hi."}]},{"cues":[{"time":7622,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8983,"text":"[Jennifer Brea is sound-sensitive."},{"time":10704,"text":"The live audience was asked\nto applaud ASL-style, in silence.]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13873,"text":"So, five years ago, this was me."},{"time":17747,"text":"I was a PhD student at Harvard,"},{"time":19776,"text":"and I loved to travel."},{"time":22472,"text":"I had just gotten engaged\nto marry the love of my life."},{"time":27072,"text":"I was 28, and like so many of us\nwhen we are in good health,"},{"time":31071,"text":"I felt like I was invincible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":34477,"text":"Then one day I had\na fever of 104.7 degrees."},{"time":38758,"text":"I probably should have gone to the doctor,"},{"time":40831,"text":"but I'd never really been sick in my life,"},{"time":43419,"text":"and I knew that usually,\nif you have a virus,"},{"time":45796,"text":"you stay home and you make\nsome chicken soup,"},{"time":48953,"text":"and in a few days,\neverything will be fine."},{"time":52499,"text":"But this time it wasn't fine."},{"time":55560,"text":"After the fever broke,"},{"time":57121,"text":"for three weeks I was so dizzy,\nI couldn't leave my house."},{"time":61467,"text":"I would walk straight into door frames."},{"time":64335,"text":"I had to hug the walls\njust to make it to the bathroom."},{"time":68613,"text":"That spring I got infection\nafter infection,"},{"time":71825,"text":"and every time I went to the doctor,"},{"time":73676,"text":"he said there was absolutely\nnothing wrong."},{"time":77533,"text":"He had his laboratory tests,"},{"time":79182,"text":"which always came back normal."},{"time":81875,"text":"All I had were my symptoms,"},{"time":83866,"text":"which I could describe,"},{"time":85820,"text":"but no one else can see."},{"time":89370,"text":"I know it sounds silly,"},{"time":90617,"text":"but you have to find a way\nto explain things like this to yourself,"},{"time":93909,"text":"and so I thought maybe I was just aging."},{"time":98114,"text":"Maybe this is what it's like\nto be on the other side of 25."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101691,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":104808,"text":"Then the neurological symptoms started."},{"time":107590,"text":"Sometimes I would find that I couldn't\ndraw the right side of a circle."},{"time":112325,"text":"Other times I wouldn't be able\nto speak or move at all."},{"time":118330,"text":"I saw every kind of specialist:"},{"time":120088,"text":"infectious disease doctors,\ndermatologists, endocrinologists,"},{"time":123184,"text":"cardiologists."},{"time":124945,"text":"I even saw a psychiatrist."},{"time":127679,"text":"My psychiatrist said,\n\"It's clear you're really sick,"},{"time":130947,"text":"but not with anything psychiatric."},{"time":134045,"text":"I hope they can find out\nwhat's wrong with you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":138094,"text":"The next day, my neurologist\ndiagnosed me with conversion disorder."},{"time":142842,"text":"He told me that everything --"},{"time":145255,"text":"the fevers, the sore throats,\nthe sinus infection,"},{"time":148916,"text":"all of the gastrointestinal,\nneurological and cardiac symptoms --"},{"time":152715,"text":"were being caused\nby some distant emotional trauma"},{"time":155457,"text":"that I could not remember."},{"time":158069,"text":"The symptoms were real, he said,"},{"time":160546,"text":"but they had no biological cause."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164527,"text":"I was training to be a social scientist."},{"time":167160,"text":"I had studied statistics,\nprobability theory,"},{"time":170416,"text":"mathematical modeling,\nexperimental design."},{"time":175058,"text":"I felt like I couldn't just reject\nmy neurologist's diagnosis."},{"time":179599,"text":"It didn't feel true,"},{"time":181215,"text":"but I knew from my training\nthat the truth is often counterintuitive,"},{"time":185356,"text":"so easily obscured\nby what we want to believe."},{"time":188514,"text":"So I had to consider the possibility\nthat he was right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":193603,"text":"That day, I ran a small experiment."},{"time":196919,"text":"I walked back the two miles\nfrom my neurologist's office to my house,"},{"time":201229,"text":"my legs wrapped in this strange,\nalmost electric kind of pain."},{"time":206475,"text":"I meditated on that pain,"},{"time":208102,"text":"contemplating how my mind\ncould have possibly generated all this."},{"time":213320,"text":"As soon as I walked through the door,"},{"time":215219,"text":"I collapsed."},{"time":216837,"text":"My brain and my spinal cord were burning."},{"time":220696,"text":"My neck was so stiff\nI couldn't touch my chin to my chest,"},{"time":225324,"text":"and the slightest sound --"},{"time":227099,"text":"the rustling of the sheets,"},{"time":228958,"text":"my husband walking barefoot\nin the next room --"},{"time":231737,"text":"could cause excruciating pain."},{"time":235832,"text":"I would spend most\nof the next two years in bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239235,"text":"How could my doctor\nhave gotten it so wrong?"},{"time":242939,"text":"I thought I had a rare disease,"},{"time":245144,"text":"something doctors had never seen."},{"time":247926,"text":"And then I went online"},{"time":249145,"text":"and found thousands of people\nall over the world"},{"time":251980,"text":"living with the same symptoms,"},{"time":254087,"text":"similarly isolated,"},{"time":255675,"text":"similarly disbelieved."},{"time":257854,"text":"Some could still work,"},{"time":259161,"text":"but had to spend their evenings\nand weekends in bed,"},{"time":261670,"text":"just so they could show up\nthe next Monday."},{"time":264364,"text":"On the other end of the spectrum,"},{"time":266468,"text":"some were so sick"},{"time":268230,"text":"they had to live in complete darkness,"},{"time":270560,"text":"unable to tolerate\nthe sound of a human voice"},{"time":273956,"text":"or the touch of a loved one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277469,"text":"I was diagnosed\nwith myalgic encephalomyelitis."},{"time":282554,"text":"You've probably heard it called\n\"chronic fatigue syndrome.\""},{"time":286987,"text":"For decades, that's a name"},{"time":288933,"text":"that's meant that this"},{"time":291578,"text":"has been the dominant image"},{"time":292985,"text":"of a disease that can be\nas serious as this."},{"time":297468,"text":"The key symptom we all share"},{"time":299016,"text":"is that whenever we exert ourselves --\nphysically, mentally --"},{"time":303296,"text":"we pay and we pay hard."},{"time":305807,"text":"If my husband goes for a run,\nhe might be sore for a couple of days."},{"time":309325,"text":"If I try to walk half a block,\nI might be bedridden for a week."},{"time":313323,"text":"It is a perfect custom prison."},{"time":316261,"text":"I know ballet dancers who can't dance,"},{"time":319033,"text":"accountants who can't add,"},{"time":321230,"text":"medical students who never became doctors."},{"time":324421,"text":"It doesn't matter what you once were;"},{"time":327056,"text":"you can't do it anymore."},{"time":329475,"text":"It's been four years,"},{"time":331389,"text":"and I've still never been as well as I was"},{"time":334009,"text":"the minute before I walked home\nfrom my neurologist's office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338683,"text":"It's estimated that about 15 to 30 million\npeople around the world"},{"time":341902,"text":"have this disease."},{"time":343604,"text":"In the US, where I'm from,\nit's about one million people."},{"time":346891,"text":"That makes it roughly twice as common\nas multiple sclerosis."},{"time":351797,"text":"Patients can live for decades\nwith the physical function"},{"time":354563,"text":"of someone with congestive heart failure."},{"time":357310,"text":"Twenty-five percent of us\nare homebound or bedridden,"},{"time":360927,"text":"and 75 to 85 percent of us\ncan't even work part-time."},{"time":365385,"text":"Yet doctors do not treat us"},{"time":368064,"text":"and science does not study us."},{"time":371116,"text":"How could a disease this common\nand this devastating"},{"time":375325,"text":"have been forgotten by medicine?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379264,"text":"When my doctor diagnosed me\nwith conversion disorder,"},{"time":381812,"text":"he was invoking a lineage\nof ideas about women's bodies"},{"time":384524,"text":"that are over 2,500 years old."},{"time":387215,"text":"The Roman physician Galen thought"},{"time":388972,"text":"that hysteria was caused\nby sexual deprivation"},{"time":391967,"text":"in particularly passionate women."},{"time":395125,"text":"The Greeks thought the uterus\nwould literally dry up"},{"time":397913,"text":"and wander around the body\nin search of moisture,"},{"time":400364,"text":"pressing on internal organs --"},{"time":402284,"text":"yes --"},{"time":404648,"text":"causing symptoms from extreme emotions"},{"time":407367,"text":"to dizziness and paralysis."},{"time":410715,"text":"The cure was marriage and motherhood."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414898,"text":"These ideas went largely unchanged\nfor several millennia until the 1880s,"},{"time":419482,"text":"when neurologists tried to modernize\nthe theory of hysteria."},{"time":423764,"text":"Sigmund Freud developed a theory"},{"time":425441,"text":"that the unconscious mind\ncould produce physical symptoms"},{"time":428261,"text":"when dealing with memories or emotions"},{"time":430300,"text":"too painful for the conscious\nmind to handle."},{"time":432635,"text":"It converted these emotions\ninto physical symptoms."},{"time":437460,"text":"This meant that men\ncould now get hysteria,"},{"time":439680,"text":"but of course women were still\nthe most susceptible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443448,"text":"When I began investigating\nthe history of my own disease,"},{"time":447089,"text":"I was amazed to find how deep\nthese ideas still run."},{"time":451011,"text":"In 1934,"},{"time":452221,"text":"198 doctors, nurses and staff\nat the Los Angeles County General Hospital"},{"time":457020,"text":"became seriously ill."},{"time":458585,"text":"They had muscle weakness, stiffness\nin the neck and back, fevers --"},{"time":463020,"text":"all of the same symptoms\nI had when I first got diagnosed."},{"time":466928,"text":"Doctors thought\nit was a new form of polio."},{"time":470133,"text":"Since then, there have been more\nthan 70 outbreaks documented"},{"time":473088,"text":"around the world,"},{"time":474273,"text":"of a strikingly similar\npost-infectious disease."},{"time":477419,"text":"All of these outbreaks have tended\nto disproportionately affect women,"},{"time":481482,"text":"and in time, when doctors failed to find\nthe one cause of the disease,"},{"time":485433,"text":"they thought that these outbreaks\nwere mass hysteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489115,"text":"Why has this idea had such staying power?"},{"time":493567,"text":"I do think it has to do with sexism,"},{"time":495387,"text":"but I also think that fundamentally,\ndoctors want to help."},{"time":498852,"text":"They want to know the answer,"},{"time":500646,"text":"and this category allows doctors to treat\nwhat would otherwise be untreatable,"},{"time":505561,"text":"to explain illnesses\nthat have no explanation."},{"time":509079,"text":"The problem is that this\ncan cause real harm."},{"time":512382,"text":"In the 1950s, a psychiatrist\nnamed Eliot Slater"},{"time":516002,"text":"studied a cohort of 85 patients\nwho had been diagnosed with hysteria."},{"time":520766,"text":"Nine years later, 12 of them were dead\nand 30 had become disabled."},{"time":524787,"text":"Many had undiagnosed conditions\nlike multiple sclerosis,"},{"time":528244,"text":"epilepsy, brain tumors."},{"time":531259,"text":"In 1980, hysteria was officially\nrenamed \"conversion disorder.\""},{"time":535563,"text":"When my neurologist gave me\nthat diagnosis in 2012,"},{"time":538911,"text":"he was echoing Freud's words verbatim,"},{"time":541552,"text":"and even today,"},{"time":542727,"text":"women are 2 to 10 times more likely\nto receive that diagnosis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548487,"text":"The problem with the theory of hysteria\nor psychogenic illness"},{"time":552510,"text":"is that it can never be proven."},{"time":554568,"text":"It is by definition\nthe absence of evidence,"},{"time":558192,"text":"and in the case of ME,"},{"time":559591,"text":"psychological explanations\nhave held back biological research."},{"time":563620,"text":"All around the world, ME is one\nof the least funded diseases."},{"time":567321,"text":"In the US, we spend each year\nroughly 2,500 dollars per AIDS patient,"},{"time":574809,"text":"250 dollars per MS patient"},{"time":578100,"text":"and just 5 dollars per year\nper ME patient."},{"time":582125,"text":"This was not just lightning."},{"time":584230,"text":"I was not just unlucky."},{"time":586494,"text":"The ignorance surrounding my disease\nhas been a choice,"},{"time":589609,"text":"a choice made by the institutions\nthat were supposed to protect us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":595535,"text":"We don't know why ME\nsometimes runs in families,"},{"time":598430,"text":"why you can get it\nafter almost any infection,"},{"time":600919,"text":"from enteroviruses\nto Epstein-Barr virus to Q fever,"},{"time":605123,"text":"or why it affects women\nat two to three times the rate of men."},{"time":609058,"text":"This issue is much bigger\nthan just my disease."},{"time":612356,"text":"When I first got sick,"},{"time":613563,"text":"old friends were reaching out to me."},{"time":616180,"text":"I soon found myself a part\nof a cohort of women in their late 20s"},{"time":619333,"text":"whose bodies were falling apart."},{"time":622012,"text":"What was striking was just how\nmuch trouble we were having"},{"time":624891,"text":"being taken seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":626577,"text":"I learned of one woman with scleroderma,"},{"time":628559,"text":"an autoimmune connective tissue disease,"},{"time":630683,"text":"who was told for years\nthat it was all in her head."},{"time":633417,"text":"Between the time of onset and diagnosis,"},{"time":635953,"text":"her esophagus was so thoroughly damaged,"},{"time":638404,"text":"she will never be able to eat again."},{"time":640673,"text":"Another woman with ovarian cancer,"},{"time":643376,"text":"who for years was told\nthat it was just early menopause."},{"time":647188,"text":"A friend from college,"},{"time":648780,"text":"whose brain tumor was misdiagnosed\nfor years as anxiety."}]},{"cues":[{"time":654222,"text":"Here's why this worries me:"},{"time":657125,"text":"since the 1950s, rates of many\nautoimmune diseases"},{"time":660600,"text":"have doubled to tripled."},{"time":662818,"text":"Forty-five percent of patients\nwho are eventually diagnosed"},{"time":665782,"text":"with a recognized autoimmune disease"},{"time":667800,"text":"are initially told they're hypochondriacs."},{"time":670783,"text":"Like the hysteria of old,\nthis has everything to do with gender"},{"time":673957,"text":"and with whose stories we believe."},{"time":676974,"text":"Seventy-five percent\nof autoimmune disease patients are women,"},{"time":680649,"text":"and in some diseases,\nit's as high as 90 percent."},{"time":685076,"text":"Even though these diseases\ndisproportionately affect women,"},{"time":687957,"text":"they are not women's diseases."},{"time":689633,"text":"ME affects children\nand ME affects millions of men."},{"time":693345,"text":"And as one patient told me,"},{"time":695154,"text":"we get it coming and going --"},{"time":696686,"text":"if you're a woman, you're told\nyou're exaggerating your symptoms,"},{"time":700318,"text":"but if you're a guy, you're told\nto be strong, to buck up."},{"time":704676,"text":"And men may even have\na more difficult time getting diagnosed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717419,"text":"My brain is not what it used to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733914,"text":"Here's the good part:"},{"time":736645,"text":"despite everything, I still have hope."},{"time":739903,"text":"So many diseases were once\nthought of as psychological"},{"time":743827,"text":"until science uncovered\ntheir biological mechanisms."},{"time":747323,"text":"Patients with epilepsy\ncould be forcibly institutionalized"},{"time":750441,"text":"until the EEG was able to measure\nabnormal electrical activity in the brain."},{"time":755500,"text":"Multiple sclerosis could be misdiagnosed\nas hysterical paralysis"},{"time":759800,"text":"until the CAT scan and the MRI\ndiscovered brain lesions."},{"time":763945,"text":"And recently, we used to think"},{"time":765484,"text":"that stomach ulcers\nwere just caused by stress,"},{"time":768328,"text":"until we discovered\nthat H. pylori was the culprit."},{"time":772801,"text":"ME has never benefited\nfrom the kind of science"},{"time":775719,"text":"that other diseases have had,"},{"time":778053,"text":"but that's starting to change."},{"time":780661,"text":"In Germany, scientists are starting\nto find evidence of autoimmunity,"},{"time":784226,"text":"and in Japan, of brain inflammation."},{"time":787406,"text":"In the US, scientists at Stanford\nare finding abnormalities"},{"time":790484,"text":"in energy metabolism"},{"time":792404,"text":"that are 16 standard deviations\naway from normal."},{"time":796640,"text":"And in Norway, researchers\nare running a phase-3 clinical trial"},{"time":800709,"text":"on a cancer drug that in some patients\ncauses complete remission."}]},{"cues":[{"time":805798,"text":"What also gives me hope"},{"time":808316,"text":"is the resilience of patients."},{"time":811968,"text":"Online we came together,"},{"time":814251,"text":"and we shared our stories."},{"time":817449,"text":"We devoured what research there was."},{"time":820743,"text":"We experimented on ourselves."},{"time":823496,"text":"We became our own scientists\nand our own doctors"},{"time":825893,"text":"because we had to be."},{"time":828378,"text":"And slowly I added five percent here,\nfive percent there,"},{"time":832141,"text":"until eventually, on a good day,"},{"time":834398,"text":"I was able to leave my home."},{"time":837815,"text":"I still had to make ridiculous choices:"},{"time":840568,"text":"Will I sit in the garden for 15 minutes,\nor will I wash my hair today?"},{"time":844924,"text":"But it gave me hope\nthat I could be treated."},{"time":847693,"text":"I had a sick body; that was all."},{"time":850789,"text":"And with the right kind of help,\nmaybe one day I could get better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855740,"text":"I came together with patients\naround the world,"},{"time":859466,"text":"and we started to fight."},{"time":861863,"text":"We have filled the void\nwith something wonderful,"},{"time":865698,"text":"but it is not enough."},{"time":868662,"text":"I still don't know if I will ever\nbe able to run again,"},{"time":872723,"text":"or walk at any distance,"},{"time":874644,"text":"or do any of those kinetic things\nthat I now only get to do in my dreams."},{"time":879143,"text":"But I am so grateful\nfor how far I have come."},{"time":883955,"text":"Progress is slow,"},{"time":885464,"text":"and it is up"},{"time":887310,"text":"and it is down,"},{"time":889222,"text":"but I am getting a little better each day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":894013,"text":"I remember what it was like\nwhen I was stuck in that bedroom,"},{"time":898548,"text":"when it had been months\nsince I had seen the sun."},{"time":903226,"text":"I thought that I would die there."},{"time":906961,"text":"But here I am today,"},{"time":909255,"text":"with you,"},{"time":911513,"text":"and that is a miracle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916606,"text":"I don't know what would have happened\nhad I not been one of the lucky ones,"},{"time":920377,"text":"had I gotten sick before the internet,"},{"time":922995,"text":"had I not found my community."},{"time":925777,"text":"I probably would have already\ntaken my own life,"},{"time":929028,"text":"as so many others have done."},{"time":932094,"text":"How many lives could\nwe have saved, decades ago,"},{"time":935957,"text":"if we had asked the right questions?"},{"time":938626,"text":"How many lives could we save today"},{"time":941592,"text":"if we decide to make a real start?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":945205,"text":"Even once the true cause\nof my disease is discovered,"},{"time":948881,"text":"if we don't change\nour institutions and our culture,"},{"time":952380,"text":"we will do this again to another disease."},{"time":955658,"text":"Living with this illness has taught me"},{"time":957676,"text":"that science and medicine\nare profoundly human endeavors."},{"time":961153,"text":"Doctors, scientists and policy makers"},{"time":963768,"text":"are not immune to the same biases"},{"time":967568,"text":"that affect all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971377,"text":"We need to think in more nuanced ways\nabout women's health."},{"time":975119,"text":"Our immune systems are just as much\na battleground for equality"},{"time":979245,"text":"as the rest of our bodies."},{"time":981253,"text":"We need to listen to patients' stories,"},{"time":984542,"text":"and we need to be willing\nto say, \"I don't know.\""},{"time":988024,"text":"\"I don't know\" is a beautiful thing."},{"time":991235,"text":"\"I don't know\" is where discovery starts."},{"time":995365,"text":"And if we can do that,"},{"time":997447,"text":"if we can approach the great vastness\nof all that we do not know,"},{"time":1001166,"text":"and then, rather than fear uncertainty,"},{"time":1003142,"text":"maybe we can greet it\nwith a sense of wonder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006342,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012096,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}